title: Grateful Dead Live at Cleveland Public Hall on 1979-11-29
lineage: SBD -> Cassette Master (Sony TCD5M/UDXL-II) -> Dat (Panasonic SV3800/48k)
description: Alabama Getaway-> Promised Land, They Love Each Other, Mama Tried-> Mexicali Blues, Althea, Easy To Love You, Minglewood Blues, Brown Eyed Women-> Looks Like Rain-> Don't Ease Me In Shakedown Street-> Samson & Delilah, High Time, Estimated Prophet-> Eyes Of The World-> Drums-> Not Fade Away-> Black Peter-> Around & Around-> Johnny B. Goode, E: U.S. Blues

reviews.review_text: i like this source better more full rich sound than the other board available.  solid fall '79 show.
CM4Prez. This is a better version of the 2 options.

This good show seems to have gone under the radar! Not many reviews but great sound and solid performance by the boys. Great TLEO and very solid Estimated leading into a terrific Eyes. The Eyes has a beautiful jam at the end of it and comes close to 20 minutes! Definitely one of the better Eyes that I've heard. Only problem with the show is Around and Around. Bobby starts off-key and the song never really gets back on its feet - a complete disaster. Other than that, though, it's a solid 4-star show.
